---
description: Enforce clean architecture boundaries and hard constraints from AGENTS.md.
globs:
  - "src/**/*.ts"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Follow boundary rules from `AGENTS.md`:
  - `domain` imports only from `shared`
  - `infra` does not import `domain/gateway/pipeline`
  - `gateway` and `pipeline` do not import `infra` directly except via dependency injection
  - `pipeline` does not import from `gateway` (only from `shared` and `domain`)
  - `shared` is a leaf
- All DB access must be user-scoped (`user_id` filtering).
- Keep user input in `user` role and separated from system instructions.
- Do not log full message text; metadata only.
- Never use `spikes/` for implementation work.
- When relevant, apply hard constraints from `docs/decisions/`.
- Import policy:
  - Default to public top-level package imports (e.g., `from "package"`).
  - Avoid deep imports into internal library paths.
  - Allow deep imports only with explicit technical justification and an inline code comment.
